    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips and add to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Strip your <strong>rosemary leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems, then sprinkle the<strong> chopped rosemary </strong>all over the chips and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until crisp \u2013 these are your <strong>rosemary chips</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-veggie-blue-cheese-burger-with-tomato-relish/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chips are cooking, chop your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>roughly</p><p>Heat a pot with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped tomato</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until beginning to break down</p><p>Whilst the tomatoes are cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-veggie-blue-cheese-burger-with-tomato-relish/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>tomato paste </strong>to the pot<strong> </strong>and cook for 30 secs further</p><p>Add 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[125ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> with your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 5-6 min or until the tomatoes have broken down and the sauce is the consistency of ketchup \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato relish</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-veggie-blue-cheese-burger-with-tomato-relish/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>meat-free burger patty[ies]</strong> to one side of a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined<strong> </strong>tray, then put the tray in the oven for an initial 10 min</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-veggie-blue-cheese-burger-with-tomato-relish/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst everything is in the oven, wash your<strong> lettuce</strong> then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Remove 2 <strong>outer leaves </strong>per person from the<strong> lettuce</strong> and chop the <strong>inner core[s]</strong> into quarters</p><p>Peel and slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong> into rounds</p><p>Slice your <strong>stilton cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-veggie-blue-cheese-burger-with-tomato-relish/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the patties have had 10 min, remove the tray from the oven and top them with the <strong>sliced stilton cheese</strong> \u2013 these are your <strong>cheesy meat-free patties</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-veggie-blue-cheese-burger-with-tomato-relish/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>brioche buns</strong> in half (if required!)</p><p>Add the<strong> brioche half[ves]</strong> to the other side of the tray</p><p>Return the tray to the oven for 2-3 min or until the <strong>cheese</strong> has melted and the brioche is warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-ultimate-veggie-blue-cheese-burger-with-tomato-relish/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Assemble your burgers by topping the <strong>warmed</strong> <strong>brioche base</strong> with a dollop of <strong>tomato relish</strong>, 2 <strong>lettuce leaves</strong>, a <strong>cheesy meat-free patty</strong>,<strong> </strong>some<strong> shallot rounds</strong> and the<strong> warmed brioche lid</strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>ultimate veggie blue cheese burger</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> ultimate veggie blue cheese burger</strong> with the <strong>rosemary chips</strong>,<strong> lettuce quarters</strong> and any <strong>remaining tomato relish</strong> to the side for dipping</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
